   {:e #blake3 "44dc49f04825effedfaa22b70101b91ac93033eb469597109018bb00d8035b9b" :a :harvest/accomplishments :v "Event sourcing pipeline: materialize engine uses deterministic fold (APP-INV-073). CausalSort via Kahn's algorithm with timestamp tiebreaker (APP-ADR-074). Stream Processors are fold observers that fire after content events (APP-INV-080). The fold is pure: events -> SQL state, replay produces identical state (idempotency, APP-INV-075). This is the most architecturally significant subsystem — it turns JSONL event streams into materialized SQL views, enabling the system to rebuild state from history.; What connects :session/s-1774293270 to :session/s-1774293357850?; Session entity: :runtime/req-0fa13a163fd5a6d6; Consistency engine implements 5-tier contradiction detection: Tier 2 (Graph — governance overlap, cycles), Tier 3 (SAT — propositional encoding via gophersat), Tier 4 (Heuristic — polarity, quantifier, numeric + LSI semantic), Tier 5 (SMT — Z3 subprocess for SMT-LIB2), Tier 6 (LLM-as-judge via Anthropic API). Tiers are executed in order, results deduplicated by element pair keeping highest confidence. 9 ConflictTypes defined. The architecture is well-decomposed: one file per tier (graph.go, sat.go, heuristic.go, semantic.go, smt.go, llm.go).; What connects :session/s-1774293270 to :session/s-1774367218?; APP-INV-002 Validation Determinism: PARTIALLY DIVERGENT. The core validation checks (14 checks in validator/checks.go) are deterministic — no rand, no time.Now, pure SQL queries. However, the Tier 6 LLM-as-Judge contradiction detector (consistency/llm.go) uses LLM calls with majority voting (3 runs, 2/3 agreement), which is inherently non-deterministic. The spec acknowledges this via APP-INV-054 (graceful degradation) and the majority vote protocol (APP-INV-055), but this creates a tension: identical specs can produce different contradiction reports depending on LLM availability and response variation. The deterministic tiers (1-5: heuristic, SAT, SMT, graph, semantic) are clean. The non-deterministic tier is optional but when active, violates the letter of INV-002.; Session entity: :runtime/req-5425757a62fb8f1f; FINDING-1: cascade.go (lines 74,84,94,127,139) silently discards 5 database errors using blank identifier. GetInvariantRegistryEntries, ListModules, GetModuleRelationships, GetBacklinks, GetModuleDomains all have their errors discarded. If the database is corrupted or a table is missing, the cascade analysis will return incomplete/wrong results with no indication that something went wrong. This violates Go error handling best practices.; Session entity: :task/t-cecad16e; Session entity: :task/t-1edd3feb; Drift analysis system measures 3 drift types: (1) ImplDrift — unspecified (code without spec), unimplemented (spec without code), contradictions (integrates consistency engine tiers 2-4); (2) IntentDrift — uncovered non-negotiables via keyword overlap heuristic; (3) ProcessDrift — witness coverage, spec-first ratio, tool intermediation, validate gating. Outputs remediation packages with priority. Planned divergences tracked in session state. Quality breakdown into correctness/depth/coherence dimensions.; Session entity: :task/t-4a0e78ca; Session entity: :runtime/req-e5fd013a8108780d; APP-INV-001 Round-Trip Fidelity: ALIGNED. The Go CLI achieves byte-identical round-trip via raw_text storage in source_files table. Both RenderMonolith and RenderModular (renderer/monolith.go, renderer/modular.go) simply retrieve and write back the stored raw_text. This is a correct but trivial implementation — it preserves fidelity by storing the original verbatim rather than reconstructing from parsed structure. Test exists: tests/roundtrip_test.go with TestRoundTripMonolith and TestRoundTripModular verifying SHA-256 equivalence. The implementation matches the spec.; Session entity: :runtime/req-2fceacf9027a07f4; Event system uses 3-stream JSONL files (APP-ADR-015): Stream 1 (Discovery — ideas, questions, decisions), Stream 2 (Specification — parse, validate, drift), Stream 3 (Implementation — issues, status, findings). Event envelope: {id, type, timestamp, spec_hash, stream, payload, causes, version}. Content-addressed by payload SHA-256. Event IDs: evt-YYYYMMDD-<16hex>. Causal ordering via causes array (APP-INV-074). Schema versioned for forward compat (APP-INV-072).; Session entity: :runtime/req-72fb90ddae448b70; What connects :session/s-1774293270 to :session/s-1774293357850?; SQLite schema has 30 tables across 5 domains: (1) Spec metadata (spec_index, source_files, modules, manifest), (2) Element storage (invariants, adrs, adr_options, negative_specs, quality_gates, sections, glossary_entries, cross_references, verification_prompts, verification_checks, meta_instructions, worked_examples, why_not_annotations, comparison_blocks, performance_budgets, budget_entries, state_machines, state_machine_cells), (3) Search (fts_index FTS5, search_vectors, search_model, search_authority), (4) Code bridge (code_annotations, invariant_witnesses, challenge_results, invariant_registry), (5) Event sourcing (transactions, tx_operations, snapshots, event_provenance, session_state, formatting_hints). This is a traditional relational schema — fundamentally different from braid's EAV datom model.; Parser implements a 4-pass pipeline (APP-ADR-009): Pass 1 builds section tree from headings, Pass 2 extracts 12 element types (invariants, ADRs, quality gates, negative specs, verification prompts, meta-instructions, worked examples, WHY-NOT annotations, comparison blocks, performance budgets, state machines, glossary entries), Pass 3 extracts cross-references, Pass 4 resolves cross-references. Supports both monolith and modular parsing. Each element type has its own recognizer file. Formatting hints recorded for round-trip fidelity (APP-INV-001).; APP-INV-073 Fold Determinism: ALIGNED. The Apply() function in materialize/fold.go is a pure switch statement over event types, dispatching to applier methods. No time.Now, no rand, no os.Getenv in the fold path. CausalSort uses Kahn's algorithm with timestamp tiebreaker for stable ordering. The only time.Now() in the package is in snapshot.go CreateSnapshot() which sets created_at metadata — this is NOT in the fold path and does not affect materialization results. The fold itself is deterministic: same events in same order produce same SQLite state. The snapshot state hash (APP-INV-093) is computed deterministically from DB content. Well-implemented.; APP-INV-071 Log Canonicality: DIVERGENT. The spec requires JSONL event log as single source of truth, with SQLite as a derived materialized view. However, the primary parse pipeline (parser/document.go ParseDocument()) writes DIRECTLY to SQLite via storage.InsertSpecIndex/InsertSourceFile/InsertSectionsDB without emitting events first. The event-sourcing pipeline (materialize/fold.go) exists as a separate code path but is NOT wired as the primary parse path. The 'import' command creates events from markdown, and 'materialize' folds events into SQLite, but 'parse' bypasses this entirely. This means SQLite is the de facto source of truth, not JSONL — directly contradicting INV-071. The two paths (legacy parse vs event-sourced import+materialize) coexist but are not unified.; DOGFOOD-2 SESSION 1 START: 3 parallel agents doing real work on Go CLI. Store 2061 datoms, M(t)=0.78; Witness system implements multi-level evidence hierarchy: Level 1 (annotation - code comment linking to invariant), Level 2 (test - test function targeting invariant), Level 3 (verify - mechanical annotation proof with --verify flag), Level 4 (review - Gestalt-framed review bundle with code snippets, review criteria, and spec context via --review-context). Auto-invalidation (APP-INV-041) when spec or code hashes change. Evidence types: test, annotation, scan, review, attestation, eval.; What connects :session/s-1774293270 to 859fc7a88cdac71b?; Code annotation system uses structured comments in source files (ddis:verb TARGET) with 8 verbs: maintains, implements, interfaces, tests, validates-via, postcondition, relates-to, satisfies. Supports 30+ languages via CommentFamily map (C-style //, hash #, SQL --, semicolon ;, HTML comments). The scan package walks code directories extracting annotations, which are stored in code_annotations table. The witness system uses these annotations to mechanically verify spec-code traceability. This is the spec-code bridge that enables bidirectional drift detection.; What connects :session/s-1774293270 to 859fc7a88cdac71b?; Session entity: :task/t-19ed4d93; Session entity: :runtime/req-e7cfad06807f90d2; FINDING-2: SMT solver (smt.go) has O(n^2) pairwise Z3 subprocess invocations. With n invariants having semi-formal expressions, it spawns up to n*(n-1)/2 Z3 processes sequentially, each with a 30-second timeout. For a spec with 97 invariants, if 50 have semi-formal expressions, that is 1225 Z3 invocations with worst-case 10+ hours runtime. No parallelism, no batching, no incremental solving. The SAT solver (sat.go) has the same O(n^2) pattern but is in-process so less costly.; Go CLI has 48 Cobra commands organized into 5 groups: Core (parse/validate/coverage/drift/next/spec/issue/triage/materialize/project), Investigation (context/search/query/exemplar/impact/cascade/contradict/history/bisect/blame), Improvement (refine/discover/absorb/witness/scan/challenge), Planning (progress/implorder/checklist/bundle/skeleton/diff/tasks), Utility (render/seed/log/tx/state/checkpoint/init/patch/manifest/agenthelp/rename/import/replay). Bare 'ddis' delegates to 'next' command.; APP-INV-010/APP-INV-020 Oplog+Event Stream Append-Only: ALIGNED. Both oplog.go and events/stream.go enforce append-only via O_APPEND|O_CREATE|O_WRONLY flags. No Seek, Truncate, or WriteAt operations exist anywhere in either package. The AppendEvent function explicitly documents the negative spec: 'A function that cannot seek cannot overwrite.' The implementation is structurally correct — the OS-level file flags prevent modification. Code annotations reference the correct spec IDs.; Search system is triple-layered: (1) FTS5 full-text search for exact/prefix queries, (2) LSI (Latent Semantic Indexing) via gonum SVD for semantic similarity (TF-IDF matrix, truncated SVD to k dimensions, cosine similarity), (3) PageRank authority scoring from cross-reference graph. The ContextBundle (search/context.go, 906 LOC) is the most important user-facing data structure - it assembles a complete pre-flight briefing for any spec element including constraints, coverage gaps, related elements, impact radius, witness status, and editing guidance.; Session entity: :task/t-c1b45639; Bilateral cycle has 4 phases: (1) discover - builds LLM context bundle with thread convergence, cognitive mode classification (exploring/narrowing/committing), guidance attenuation by depth, and open question tracking; (2) refine - applies spec modifications with bidirectional sync; (3) absorb - reconciles code patterns against spec with 3 categories: correspondences (matched), undocumented behavior (code without spec), unimplemented spec (spec without code). Uses keyword overlap scoring with threshold 0.6/0.4; (4) drift - measures divergence as described in prior observation. The autoprompt package provides LLM prompt generation across these phases.; What connects :session/s-1774293270 to :session/s-1774367218?" :op :assert}
